Installing Nginx Server How To Install Nginx on Ubuntu 18.04[^1] Introduction Nginx is one of the most popular web servers in the world and is responsible for hosting some of the largest and highest-traffic sites on the internet. It is more resource-friendly than Apache in most cases and can be used as a web server or reverse proxy.
Installing Nginx Install on Ubuntu 18.04 with &hellip;
sudo apt install nginx  FIrewall (optional) After accepting the procedure, apt will install Nginx and any required dependencies to your server.
